# =============================================================
# .env  —  Dataverse News API Keys
# =============================================================
# IMPORTANT: NEVER commit this file to GitHub/GitLab.
# It is listed in .gitignore for your protection.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file:   cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in your real API keys below (replace the placeholder text)
#   3. Save the file
#   4. Restart the dev server: Ctrl+C  then  npm run dev
#
# All three APIs are FREE and work in both localhost AND production.
# =============================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------
# API KEY 1: TheNewsAPI.com  (PRIMARY SOURCE)
# -----------------------------------------------------------
# Free plan : 250 requests/day
# Production: YES — works on any domain, no restrictions
# Images    : YES — "image_url" field, consistently populated
# Search    : YES — /news/all?search=keyword endpoint
# Response  : { data: [ { uuid, title, description, image_url,
#               url, published_at, source, categories } ] }
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR KEY:
#   1. Go to   https://www.thenewsapi.com
#   2. Click "Get Free API Token" or "Sign Up"
#   3. Register with your name + email + password
#   4. Check your email and verify your account
#   5. Log in → you'll see your API token on the dashboard
#   6. It looks like: abc123XYZ...  (a long alphanumeric string)
#   7. Paste it below:
VITE_THENEWSAPI_KEY=your_thenewsapi_token_here


# -----------------------------------------------------------
# API KEY 2: GNews.io  (FALLBACK #1)
# -----------------------------------------------------------
# Free plan : 100 requests/day, up to 10 articles per request
# Production: YES — works on any domain
# Images    : YES — "image" field, usually populated
# Search    : YES — /search?q=keyword endpoint
# Response  : { totalArticles: N, articles: [ { title,
#               description, image, url, publishedAt,
#               source: { name, url } } ] }
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR KEY:
#   1. Go to   https://gnews.io/register
#   2. Sign up with your email
#   3. Verify your email via the link sent to you
#   4. Log in → go to https://gnews.io/dashboard
#   5. Your API token is shown at the top of the dashboard
#   6. Paste it below:
VITE_GNEWS_KEY=your_gnews_key_here


# -----------------------------------------------------------
# API KEY 3: Currents API  (FALLBACK #2)
# -----------------------------------------------------------
# Free plan : 600 requests/day — most generous free tier!
# Production: YES — works on any domain
# Images    : SOMETIMES — "image" field can be null or "None"
#             (the app automatically uses a placeholder when missing)
# Search    : NO — search not available on free plan
# Response  : { status: "ok", news: [ { id, title, description,
#               image, url, published, author, category } ] }
#
# NOTE: Currents uses "published" (not "publishedAt") for the date.
#       The normaliser in newsService.js handles this automatically.
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR KEY:
#   1. Go to   https://currentsapi.services/en/register
#   2. Fill in your name, email, and password
#   3. Check your email and click the verification link
#   4. Log in → go to https://currentsapi.services/en/profile
#   5. Your API key is listed under "Your API Key"
#   6. It looks like: xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx  (UUID format)
#   7. Paste it below:
VITE_CURRENTS_KEY=your_currents_key_here


# -----------------------------------------------------------
# API KEY 4: The Guardian Open Platform  (FULL ARTICLE CONTENT)
# -----------------------------------------------------------
# Free plan : 5000 requests/day — very generous!
# Production: YES — explicitly allowed for commercial use (check T&C)
# Images    : YES — thumbnail field, good quality
# Full text : YES — fields.body contains the COMPLETE article HTML
#             This is the ONLY major free API that gives full body text.
# Archive   : YES — 2.7 million articles going back to 1999
#
# WHAT THIS ENABLES IN YOUR APP:
#   - Guardian articles show with "Full Article" badge on cards
#   - Click any card → full article text renders inside your website
#   - For non-Guardian articles → Guardian is searched for coverage
#     of the same topic to show full content
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR KEY:
#   1. Go to   https://open-platform.theguardian.com/access/
#   2. Click "Register for Developer Access"
#   3. Fill in: name, email, company/project name, brief description
#      (just say "personal news aggregator project")
#   4. Check your email — key arrives within seconds to a few minutes
#   5. Key looks like: xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx (UUID format)
#   6. Paste it below:
VITE_GUARDIAN_KEY=your_guardian_key_here
